TITLE: Writing to a Contract with thirdweb Engine API in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code performs a write operation on a blockchain contract through the Engine API. It calls the transferFrom function with specific parameters, requires gas funds, and returns a queueId that can be used to track the transaction status.
SOURCE: https://github.com/thirdweb-dev/js/blob/main/apps/portal/src/app/engine/get-started/page.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const resp = await fetch(
	"<engine_url>/contract/<chain>/<contract_address>/write",
	{
		method: "POST",
		headers: {
			"Content-Type": "application/json",
			Authorization: "Bearer <access_token>",
			"x-backend-wallet-address": "<backend_wallet_address>",
		},
		body: JSON.stringify({
			functionName: "transferFrom",
			args: [
				"0x1946267d81Fb8aDeeEa28e6B98bcD446c8248473",
				"0x3EcDBF3B911d0e9052b64850693888b008e18373",
				"0",
			],
		}),
	},
);

const { result } = await resp.json();
// queueId is a reference to the transaction queued by Engine.
console.log("Queue ID:", result.queueId);
```

