TITLE: ERC20Base mintTo Function Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Overridable function that allows authorized addresses to mint tokens to a specified recipient. Includes authorization and amount validation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/thirdweb-dev/js/blob/main/apps/portal/src/app/contracts/build/base-contracts/erc-20/base/page.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: solidity
CODE:
```
/**
 *  @notice          Lets an authorized address mint tokens to a recipient.
 *  @dev             The logic in the `_canMint` function determines whether the caller is authorized to mint tokens.
 *
 *  @param _to       The recipient of the tokens to mint.
 *  @param _amount   Quantity of tokens to mint.
 */
function mintTo(address _to, uint256 _amount) public virtual {
    require(_canMint(), "Not authorized to mint.");
    require(_amount != 0, "Minting zero tokens.");

    _mint(_to, _amount);
