TITLE: Retrieving Top Collections with Collection Explorer API in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the implementation of getTopCollections method, which retrieves top collections based on specific metrics like sales volume. It accepts parameters for pagination, direction, and time window for the calculation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/thirdweb-dev/js/blob/main/apps/portal/src/app/account/account-info/page.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Get collections by sales/volume
 *
 * @example
 * ```javascript
 * const topCollections = await sdk.getTopCollections();
 * ```
 *
 * @param options - Options for the request.
 * @returns The collections sorted by sales volume
 */
async getTopCollections({
  count = 100,
  start = 0,
  direction = SortDirection.DESC,
  window = StatsTimeInterval.DAY,
}: QueryAllParams & {
  direction?: SortDirection;
  window?: StatsTimeInterval;
}) {
  return await this.collectionService.getTopCollections({
    count,
    start,
    sortBy: { field: "sales.volume", direction },
    window,
  });
}
```

