TITLE: Complex Event Filtering Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Example of using multiple filter parameters to query events with specific criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/thirdweb-dev/js/blob/main/apps/portal/src/app/insight/agents-and-llms/llmstxt/page.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async function getFilteredEvents() {
	const params = new URLSearchParams({
		filter_block_number_gte: "{{startBlock}}",
		filter_block_number_lte: "{{endBlock}}",
		filter_block_timestamp_gte: "{{startTimestamp}}",
		filter_from_address: "{{fromAddress}}",
		filter_value_gte: "{{minValue}}",
		page: "0",
		limit: "20",
		sort_by: "block_timestamp",
		sort_order: "desc",
	});

	const response = await fetch(
		`https://{{chainId}}.insight.thirdweb.com/v1/events?${params}`,
		{ headers: { "x-client-id": "{{clientId}}" } },
	);
	return await response.json();
}
```

